law.text:
After all campaign expenditures have been made and before filing a final campaign finance report under Subtitle 3 of this title, any remaining balance in the account of a campaign finance entity shall be returned pro rata to the contributors or paid to:
if the campaign finance entity is a personal treasurer or a political committee formed to support a candidate or act for a political party:
the State central committee of the political party:
of which the candidate is a member; or
for which the political committee is acting;
the local central committee of the political party:
of which the candidate is a member in a county in which the candidate resides or which the candidate seeks to represent; or
for which the political committee is acting;
the board of education of a county in which the candidate resides or which the candidate seeks to represent;
a nonprofit organization that provides services or funds for the benefit of pupils or teachers;
a charitable organization registered or exempt from registration under the Maryland Charitable Solicitations Act; or
a public or private institution of higher education in the State if:
that institution possesses a certificate of approval from the Maryland Higher Education Commission; and
the payment is designated for use by the institution solely to award scholarships, grants, or loans to students attending the institution.
